hopobject.body: No, I'm not particularly sporty bedfordhousemedicalcentre.co.uk And yet, look at markets: Stocks are off mildly, with the S&P 500 only about 2 percent off its recent highs. The Vix, the so-called fear index, has risen sharply in the past week, but is at levels which if viewed historically don’t indicate anything approaching panic. Treasuries too have been calm, with some indications that investors are positioning themselves for the possibility of a near miss, but nothing extreme.
